Interface PersistenceBackendFactory

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractPersistenceBackendFactory, BlueprintsPersistenceBackendFactory, HBasePersistenceBackendFactory, MapDbPersistenceBackendFactory

    public interface PersistenceBackendFactory
    A factory of PersistenceBackend and PersistentStore.

    The creation can be configured using Resource.save(Map) and Resource.load(Map) option maps.

    See Also:
    PersistenceOptionsBuilder

      • createPersistentStore

        PersistentStore createPersistentStore(PersistentResource resource,
                                      PersistenceBackend backend,
                                      Map<?,?> options)
                               throws InvalidDataStoreException,
                                      IllegalArgumentException
        Creates a PersistentStore between the given resource and the given backend according to the given options.

        The returned PersistentStore may be a succession of several PersistentStore.

        Parameters:
        resource - the resource
        backend - the back-end
        options - the options that defines the behaviour of the back-end
        Returns:
        the newly created persistent store.
        Throws:
        InvalidDataStoreException - if there is at least one invalid value in options, or if an option is missing
        IllegalArgumentException - if the given backend is not an instance of the targeted PersistenceBackend for this factory
